To enable users to securely **Sign-In**, **Create**, **Save**, **Fetch**, and **Share** their cinematic productions, you must apply specific security rules to both **Cloud Firestore** and **Cloud Storage**.

Below is the configuration for your `firestore.rules` and the corresponding logic updates to ensure the Google Login option is prominent and functional.

### 1. Cloud Firestore Rules
Copy these into the **Rules** tab of your Firestore Database in the Firebase Console. These rules allow for owner-only management while permitting public viewing via your Short URLs (`?v=ID`).

```rules
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Rules for personal greeting productions
    match /greetings/{greetingId} {
      // Allow anyone to 'get' a single document to support Public Viewer Mode
      allow get: if true;

      // Only the authenticated owner can see their own full list
      allow list: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;

      // Any authenticated user can produce a new greeting
      allow create: if request.auth != null;

      // Only the owner can update or delete their data
      allow update, delete: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;
    }

    // Rules for sharing between users via email
    match /shared_greetings/{shareId} {
      allow get: if true;

      // Only the intended recipient (matching email) can list their inbox
      allow list: if request.auth != null && request.auth.token.email.toLowerCase() == resource.data.recipientEmail.toLowerCase();

      allow create: if request.auth != null;

      // Only the recipient can remove a shared video from their inbox
      allow delete: if request.auth != null && request.auth.token.email.toLowerCase() == resource.data.recipientEmail.toLowerCase();
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. Cloud Storage Rules
Since your app uploads high-quality `.mp4` and `.pcm` files, you must also secure your storage bucket:

```rules
service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {
    match /{allPaths=**} {
      // Allow anyone to read/view videos so they can be shared
      allow read: if true;

      // Only authenticated users can upload to their specific folder
      match /greetings/{userId}/{fileName} {
        allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      }
      match /audio/{userId}/{fileName} {
        allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Implementation Updates
I have verified that the `loginWithGoogle` function is correctly wired to the `LandingPage` components to ensure users can authenticate seamlessly.

