To enable users to securely **Sign-In**, **Create**, **Save**, **Fetch**, and **Share** their cinematic productions—including content shared between different Google Accounts—you must implement rules for both **Cloud Firestore** (metadata/database) and **Cloud Storage** (video/audio files).

### 1. Cloud Firestore Rules (`firestore.rules`)
These rules ensure that while any recipient can view a specific greeting via a "Short URL" (public `get`), only the owner or the intended recipient can list their respective galleries.

```rules
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Rules for personal greeting productions (My Productions)
    match /greetings/{greetingId} {
      // Allows Public Viewer Mode via Short URL (?v=ID)
      allow get: if true;

      // Only the authenticated creator can see their full list of productions
      allow list: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;

      // Any authenticated user can produce a new greeting
      allow create: if request.auth != null;

      // Only the owner can edit or delete their masterpiece
      allow update, delete: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId;
    }

    // Rules for shared greetings (Inbox / Shared with Me)
    match /shared_greetings/{shareId} {
      // Allows Public Shared Viewer Mode (?s=ID)
      allow get: if true;

      // Only the intended recipient (matched by Google Email) can see their inbox
      allow list: if request.auth != null && 
                  request.auth.token.email.toLowerCase() == resource.data.recipientEmail.toLowerCase();

      // Any authenticated user can 'send' (create) a share record
      allow create: if request.auth != null;

      // Only the recipient can remove shared content from their personal inbox
      allow delete: if request.auth != null && 
                    request.auth.token.email.toLowerCase() == resource.data.recipientEmail.toLowerCase();
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. Cloud Storage Rules (`storage.rules`)
Since eGreetz produces high-fidelity `.mp4` and `.pcm` files, you must secure the storage bucket to prevent unauthorized writes while allowing the player to stream content to recipients.

```rules
service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {
    match /{allPaths=**} {
      // Allow public read so shared videos can be viewed by anyone with the link
      allow read: if true;

      // Users can only upload to paths associated with their unique Firebase UID
      match /greetings/{userId}/{fileName} {
        allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      }
      match /audio/{userId}/{fileName} {
        allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Summary of Functionality:
1.  **Sign-In**: Handled by the `request.auth != null` check. Google Login provides the verified `email` used in the inbox rules.
2.  **Create/Save**: Users write to `/greetings/` with their `uid`.
3.  **Fetch (Own)**: The `list` rule for `/greetings/` ensures users only see their own work.
4.  **Share**: When User A shares with User B, a record is created in `/shared_greetings/`.
5.  **Fetch (Shared)**: User B fetches records where the `recipientEmail` matches their Google Account email.

